From Juliana Taiwo-Obalonye, Abuja President Muhammadu Buhari has extended the tenure of the Governor Mai Mala Buni-led Caretaker/Extraordinary National Convention Planning Committee for another six months. This is even as the National Executive Council has approved the expulsion of former National Vice Chairman of the party in the South-South, Ntufam Hilliard Eta, for failure to withdraw the court case instituted against the caretaker committee. The APC NEC also dissolved all states, zonal and National Party structures. The Governor of Kaduna State, Nasir El-Rufai briefed State House Correspondents with the governors of Imo, Hope Uzodinma, Ondo, Rotimi Akeredolu. 